      About this item

      • Wireless Solar Charging & Easy installation: Built-in solar panel, security cameras wireless outdoor allow you to truly get rid of tangled wires, just place the outdoor camera under the solar energy to charge, realizing 365 days of solar energy use continuously. Simply press the power button and follow the in-app instructions to connect the security camera to your 2.4GHz Wi-Fi easily. Not support 5GHz WiFi
      • Crystal 2K Image & Color Night Vision: Compared with 1080P image, the wireless camera outdoor provides you with a sharper image at 2K Resolution, which reproduces the lifelike images, allowing you to view every detail of your outdoor area and prevent threats or intruders. During the nighttime, the security camera outdoor spotlight turns on automatically, offering you clear images even in pitch black. Only work with 2.4Ghz WiFi
      • AI Human Detection Siren & Intelligent Spotlight: The wireless security camera outdoor with PIR motion sensor and automatic spotlight provide you and your family a full-protection on your safety and property. When the wireless camera outdoor detects unexpected visitors approaching your house, it will trigger an audible alarm and automatically turn on the night spotlight to scare the intruders and send you instant notifications, so you can maintain a peace of mind even when you're not at home
      • SD Card & Cloud Storage (optional): The outdoor security camera supports 24/7 motion recording to a micro SD card (up to 128GB, not included) and Cloud Storage service (optional). Additionally, it is compatible with Alexa, so you can ask their assistants to show you any location where the Wi-Fi camera outdoor wireless is recording. Not support 24/7 continuous recording
      • Two-Way Audio & Muti-User Sharing & All weather protected: The outdoor cameras for home security with microphone and speaker to ensure clear and real-time remote calls to your family or friends, and even warn off intruders at the door. You can share your camera remotely with your family from anywhere, and they can also access to the solar security cameras with you simultaneously. It is waterproof to withstand any bad weather

          Works with Alexa

          Connect your security cameras wireless outdoor to the Alexa device, then their assistants will display cameras for home security live feed with your voice commands. Note: the wireless camera is not allowed to be viewed on their APPs.

          Sharing with Multiple Users

          The outdoor camera make it more convenient for you to share your wireless security camera outdoor with your family members or friends from everywhere at any time, so they can view the solar camera outdoor wireless with you simultaneously.

          • Does this wireless camera support 5G Wi-Fi?

            No, it doesn't support 5G Wi-Fi, it can only connect to 2.4Ghz Wi-Fi.

          • Does the outdoor camera wireless S1 support 24/7 continuous recording?

            No, it doesn't support 24/7 continuous recording as it is a low-power camera with requiring power-saving for a balance battery-powered working status. But it can detect and record motion via PIR, generating motion alerts and save them in the app.

          • Does the outdoor security camera support SD card or cloud storage?

            Yes, you can use both or select one that you need. Pls note that the micro SD card is not included, and it needs to be formatted as FAT32; Its max capacity is 128GB. The Cloud storage is optional.

          • How to enable Motion Alert and receive alert notifications?

            Please enable the Motion Alert feature on the app first. Go to Camera Settings -- Enable Motion Alert -- Select Time Schedule, then please find General Settings and check if alert notifications are enabled.

          • What should I do if the camera won't hold a charge or the battery drains quickly?

            You can customize the sensitivity level to reduce false alarms, and toggle the power saving mode to conserve battery power. We recommend placing the camera in direct sunlight with enough solar power to ensure the camera stays charged.

          Amazon Customer
          5 out of 5 stars
          A great product
          Ive been reluctant to get solar cameras as I have heard nothing but bad about them. But these cameras works great! They are worth the purchase price even without a cloud based service plan (but you get a lot of extra features with a plan). I check all alerts every morning.I purchased a kit of 4 cameras. The setup was a breeze, I did it manually as I could not get the first one to see the bar code. Manual is faster for me anyways. I used some old 4gb and 8gb SD memory cards I had lying around so I used them. I try to avoid monthly service fees. When I first received them as I set each one up I put it on a charger even though none were below 86% battery power left. I went ahead and updated all cameras to latest firmware.Not fully trusting solar power I decided to test them after fully charging all of them by plugging them in, in case I needed to return them. I turned one camera off and placed it back in the box. I placed 2 cameras (turned on) in my office so I could see how the batteries would hold up without sunlight. I mounted one outside in the sun. I played with the all different settings for 3 days on all cameras, testing the motion alerts and reviewing videos.At the end of 3 days of torture test, overall Im extremely pleased, enough so that I mounted all the cameras outside. Im keeping them.I continued using/testing the cameras for about 2 weeks before placing review. Just to make sure everything was ok. I later tested multiple SD cards up to 64gb. SD card size and speed does NOT seem to make an any difference.Now for the good and the bad.THE GOODThe batteries performed better than I expected. After close to 72 hours the 2 cameras hidden from light but working, recording video and even using the bright lights for motion detection, the batteries in both cameras never dropped below 88%! So cloudy days wont be a problem for these cameras. The camera I turned off during testing was still at 100% when turned back on. On the camera mounted outdoors the battery never dropped below 99%. So solar using batteries shouldnt be a problem. Great relief as I have had problems getting power to cameras before.The quality of video recording is very good, see video of neighbors cat entering/entering my yard. The flash from dark to well-lit is when the camera's white lights turn on. Controllable in software.Had a bad storm come through a few days ago. 40mph winds and 3 inches of rain for hours. ALL cameras held up just great. No water issues that I can see.THE BAD (somewhat)Overall the hardware ( the cameras themselves) are fine, however the software could use a little tweaking. I do like the grouping feature where I can watch all 4 at once (see pict). All weaknesses appear to be fault of software and/or settings that we cant change.Video recording sometimes starts too late. Sometimes you never see the actual motion that triggered the alert, saving an extra second or 2 at the start would solve that but its not user selectable. :-(  Most times this isnt an issue if the motion continues in the video, but sometimes the object has moved outside of area recording too fast to be seen very well, especially when using far detection.Far detection works ( for me upto 80 feet away or more. However I feel it is unnecessary as you would not be able to distinguish any identifiable features of any person or object.I feel the default setting of max 10 seconds for recording is sufficient most times but a little too short in some cases. 15 seconds would be ideal but you cant change that when using SD memory cards. You have to purchase a service plan to extend that. I have other cameras also using Wansview software that record up to 20 seconds without a service plan and record the actual beginning of detection. So that is definitely a software setting.OVERALLMaybe it should be 4 3/4 stars as I would like an extra second at the start of recordings. Of course as you can tell Im really picky.
